==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Brit''' (''plural'' '''Brits''')

====Etymology====
Shortened from '''Briton'''.  ''From Anglo-Saxon '''Bryton''' or '''Briton''', an inhabitant of Britain (or of Britany, which was sometimes used interchangeably with Britain). The short form '''Brit''' (or '''Bryt''') apparently was used during the Saxon era.''

#(''informal'') A [[Briton]].

<!--Also a noun: something to do with fish.-->

